Heat oven to 375 F. Stir together graham cracker crumbs, flour and baking powder in small bowl; set aside. Beat sweetened condensed milk and butter until smooth; add reserved crumb mixture, mixing well. Stir in coconut, baking pieces and holiday bits. Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack. Cool completely. About 3 dozen cookies. Variation: Use 1-3/4 cups (10-oz. pkg.) Hershey's Mini Kisses Milk Chocolate or Semi-Sweet Baking Pieces and 1 cup coarsely chopped walnuts. Omit Holiday Bits. Proceed as directed above.